    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\n**4 files to touch, 1 new file to create:**\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + define `StatsArgs` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`).\n\n2. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Iterates `CacheBucket::iter()`, calls `DiskUsage::new(vec![cache.bucket(bucket)]).count_ignoring_errors()` per bucket, prints `\"{bucket}: {size}\"` lines then a `\"total: {size}\"` line. Skips `DiskUsage` entirely (returns 0) when a bucket directory doesn't exist. No preview guard needed.\n\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` + `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside the existing `cache_size` entries.\n\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm `CacheCommand::Stats(args) => commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` right after the `Size` arm (note: no `globals.preview` argument, unlike `cache_size`).\n\n**Key findings from exploration:**\n- `CacheBucket::iter()` yields 10 variants (not 11 — `Python` is intentionally omitted from the iterator)\n- Bucket display names come from `to_str()` via the `Display` impl: `\"wheels-v6\"`, `\"sdists-v9\"`, etc.\n- `human_readable_bytes` is already re-exported in `mod.rs` from `uv_console` — no new imports needed there",
